@host = http://localhost:3000
@baseUrl = {{host}}/api/v1
@token = Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### ============================================
### WEBHOOKS MODULE - Event Webhooks
### ============================================

### WEBHOOKS - List Webhooks
GET {{baseUrl}}/webhooks?page=1&limit=20&status=active
Authorization: {{token}}

### WEBHOOKS - Get Webhook
GET {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/:webhookId
Authorization: {{token}}

### WEBHOOKS - Create Webhook
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhooks
Authorization: {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Contact Created Event",
  "url": "https://example.com/webhook/contact-created",
  "events": ["contact.created", "contact.updated"],
  "active": true
}

### WEBHOOKS - Update Webhook
PUT {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/:webhookId
Authorization: {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://example.com/webhook/updated",
  "events": ["contact.created", "contact.updated", "contact.deleted"]
}

### WEBHOOKS - Delete Webhook
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/:webhookId
Authorization: {{token}}

### WEBHOOKS - Test Webhook
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/:webhookId/test
Authorization: {{token}}

### DELIVERIES - Get Webhook Deliveries
GET {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/:webhookId/deliveries?page=1&limit=20
Authorization: {{token}}

### Notes:
### - All endpoints require authentication
### - Event types: *.created, *.updated, *.deleted
### - Replace UUIDs with actual IDs from your database
